# SolidStart Routing and Layout Boundaries

> **Thesis:** Route groups `(private)` and `(public)` organize auth boundaries
> without adding URL segments. Layout files and `PRIVATE_ROUTES` must stay in
> sync so SSR and SPA navigation agree.

**Reference files:** `frontend/src/routes/(private).tsx`,
`frontend/src/routes/(public).tsx`, `frontend/src/lib/constants.ts`,
`frontend/src/app.tsx`, navigation components under `frontend/src/components/organisms/navigation/`.

## Route Groups Do Not Change URLs

SolidStart groups like `(private)` and `(public)` are path-transparent.
Files under `frontend/src/routes/(private)/dashboard/index.tsx` serve `/dashboard`,
not `/(private)/dashboard`.

```tsx
// Layout boundary — auth required
frontend/src/routes/(private).tsx

// Page — URL is /dashboard
frontend/src/routes/(private)/dashboard/index.tsx

// Public auth pages — URL is /login
frontend/src/routes/(public)/login/index.tsx
```

Do not duplicate the same URL under both groups. One route file owns each path.

## Private vs Public Layouts

- **`(public).tsx`** — no auth required. Landing (`/`) is full-bleed; auth pages
  use constrained width.
- **`(private).tsx`** — auth required. SSR middleware redirects unauthenticated
  users; client-side effect in the layout is a safety net for SPA navigation.

When adding a protected page:

1. Place it under `frontend/src/routes/(private)/`.
2. Add the path to `PRIVATE_ROUTES` in `frontend/src/lib/constants.ts` — SSR auth
   redirects won't work without this.
3. Use `redirectTo` (not `return`, `next`, or `redirect`) for login redirects.

## Audit The Whole Shell

`app.tsx` root layout wraps every route. When changing auth or navigation:

- Navbar links and active states
- Sidebar visibility (private routes only)
- Footer variants
- Root layout spacing tied to private-route detection

A page can render correctly while global chrome still shows wrong links or
sidebar state for the route group.

## Auth Guards in Layout vs Page

- **Layout-level:** `(private).tsx` blocks unauthenticated access to all child routes.
- **Page-level:** role or resource checks (e.g., admin-only) belong in the page
  component. Prefer `<Show when={...} fallback={...}>` over early returns before
  reactive setup — early returns skip signal creation and break re-renders when
  async guards later pass.

## Verify In A Browser

After routing or chrome changes, reproduce in a real browser. Architecture tests
can assert imports and source shape, but Solid Router interception, layout
persistence, and global shell behavior are runtime facts.

